commit_message:
Creates list of tissue IDs that need extracting from VCF

Duplicates MZs not present in UK10K data but ARE present in RNA-seq tissue data.

10G per individual achieved.

~4-7 hour run time depending on individual. ~ 10Gb per sample for all resulting output.
Added reference ASE step for comparison.
using $DIRTMP in SLURM to speed up I/O
Fixed MultiMapping script to work on correct coords.
Off by one error. VCF one-based, BAM zero-based
updated fix for duplicate variant contexts

Changed RG in STAR.

As Maternal BAM is used as a template when selecting the best reads [min: NM] the RG needs to read maternal even for the paternal haplotype BAM.
removed adapter sequences - Opted for automatic detection.
Updated filepaths for Ubuntu virtual cluster
incorrect file path for last deletion step

Created move.sh

Move BAMs from place of download to analysis folder (with a structured directory tree to hold all results).

Batch job ready

workflow.sh all.samples.txt UK10K.samples.txt 8

Specify a file with all samples RNA-seq'd, UK10K cells with genotypes that will be personalised, and how many threads to use.

Added gene level summarization 

Walked through pipeline for bugs + added gene level summary calculation using liftedOver GTFs.
Update and rename pipeline.py to consolidated_bam.py
Corrected .Map > 0-base, Corrected bisect.left to account for pairs (0,8)(9,12)
Consensus BAM function works, added Haplotype specific tags - needs cleaning as there arew redundant test functions
translateMappedPosition x 1000 quicker thanks to bisect func. Whole haplotype conversion to ref in ~ 3mins
TranslateMappedPos x1000 faster. Whole haplotype conversion in 3 minutes
Fixed bug in handling chrM (no coord change)
Pat and Pat translated Coord dicts
